From b5e3798d37d71053f3d9f119307b1134bc09439f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nick Hainke <vincent@systemli.org>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 11:07:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] grub-core/lib/gnulib: fix build failure on musl due to
 missing sys/cdefs.h

In GRUB 2.14 the gnulib-generated getopt-cdefs.h changed the include
guard for sys/cdefs.h from '#if 0' to '#if 1'. sys/cdefs.h is a
glibc/BSD-specific header not present in musl, causing a fatal build
error when compiling host utilities (grub2-editenv, grub2-bios-setup).

Revert the guard to '#if 0'. The fallback macro definitions that follow
in the file are sufficient.

Signed-off-by: Nick Hainke <vincent@systemli.org>
---
--- a/grub-core/lib/gnulib/getopt-cdefs.h
+++ b/grub-core/lib/gnulib/getopt-cdefs.h
@@ -28,7 +28,7 @@
 /* getopt-core.h and getopt-ext.h are shared with GNU libc, and expect
    a number of the internal macros supplied to GNU libc's headers by
    sys/cdefs.h.  Provide fallback definitions for all of them.  */
-#if 1
+#if 0
 # include <sys/cdefs.h>
 #endif
 
